distribution_process_identifier.documentation: Identifier an NBI or fusion reaction process intervening affecting a distribution function

distribution_process_identifier.reactant.documentation: For nuclear reaction source, energy of the reactants. index = 0 for a sum over all energies; index = 1 for thermal-thermal; index = 2 for beam-beam; index = 3 for beam-thermal

distribution_process_identifier.nbi_ener.documentation: For NBI source, energy of the accelerated species considered. index = 0 for a sum over all energies; index = 1 for full energiy; index = 2 for half energy; index = 3 for third energy

distribution_process_identifier.nbi_unit.documentation: Index of the NBI unit considered. Refers to the "unit" array of the NBI IDS. 0 means sum over all NBI units.

distribution_process_identifier.nbi_ener.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list)

distribution_process_identifier.type.documentation: Process type. index=1 for NBI; index=2 for nuclear reaction (reaction unspecified); index=3 for nuclear reaction: T(d,n)4He [D+T->He4+n]; index=4 for nuclear reaction: He3(d,p)4He [He3+D->He4+p]; index=5 for nuclear reaction: D(d,p)T [D+D->T+p]; index=6 for nuclear reaction: D(d,n)3He [D+D->He3+n]; index=7 for runaway processes

distribution_process_identifier.reactant.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list)

distribution_process_identifier.type.ind.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list)

distribution_process_identifier.nbi_beam.documentation: Index of the NBI beamlets group considered. Refers to the "unit/beamlets_group" array of the NBI IDS. 0 means sum over all beamlets groups.
